<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MINOR FLOODING DAMAGES 7 BEVERLY CENTER 
STORES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A broken sprinkler main on the seventh floor of the Beverly Center shopping 
mall at La Cienega and Beverly boulevards caused minor damage in seven stores 
Thursday, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Fire crews responding to a 1:10 p.m. call found water gushing from a sprinkler 
main that apparently had been damaged in a construction accident. The water 
flowed or dripped into three stores on the seventh floor and four shops on the 
sixth. Battalion Chief Larry Schneider said the damage was minimized because 
plastic sheeting was placed over merchandise after the problem was discovered. 
</P>
<P>
All the stores remained open. 
</P>
