SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: VISTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 19-year-old man has been arrested in an attempted rape, burglary and assault 
in Vista, the Sheriff's Department reported. 
</P>
<P>
Gale P. Lancaster of Vista was arrested Wednesday and is being held on $15,000 
bail in the County Jail in Vista on suspicion of first-degree burglary, assault 
with a deadly weapon and assault with intent to rape in connection with an 
April 23 attack on a woman at her Vista home. She reportedly said he pulled out 
a knife while they were on her patio, forced her into her residence, and 
attempted to take her upstairs. 
</P>
<P>
