SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A thief who is suspected of robbing several banks in San Diego County entered a 
Point Loma bank Thursday and left with $1,643, police said. 
</P>
<P>
It was the 13th bank the robber has hit since Feb. 8, said police spokesman 
Bill Robinson. 
</P>
<P>
The thief walked into Home Federal Bank in the 1100 block of Rosecrans 
Boulevard at 9:50 a.m. and gave the teller a note saying he had a gun and 
wanted money, Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
The robber is described as black, in his late 20s or early 30s, between 
5-foot-7, and 5-foot-9, and weighing 150 to 165 pounds. He usually wears a dark 
blue suit and sunglasses, Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
The robber was last seen walking west on Addison Street. 
</P>
