SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN YSIDRO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two people were wounded Thursday in San Ysidro when a man police believe was 
arguing with another man over smuggling migrant workers across the border 
opened fire, a police spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Bill Robinson said the two men were arguing in the parking lot of the El Pollo 
restaurant in the 3000 block of Beyer Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
Tommy Mitchell, 36, was shot three times by the other man, who fled and is at 
large, police said. 
</P>
