<P>
SUSPECT ARRESTED IN ATTACK WITH ICE PICK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROLYN KUSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 42-year-old transient has been arrested on suspicion of threatening his 
younger brother with an ice pick, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Valion Randy Jordan was arrested at a Thousand Oaks restaurant, where he fled 
after trying to slash his 28-year-old brother with an ice pick during a family 
argument, said Lt. Bill Montijo of the Ventura County Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
Jordan's brother, whom police did not identify, was not injured in the attack, 
which occurred in the 2900 block of Molly Court, Montijo said. 
</P>
<P>
At the restaurant, Jordan briefly brandished a screwdriver in an attempt to 
prevent police from approaching him, Montijo said. 
</P>
<P>
He was being held Thursday in Ventura County Jail in lieu of $10,500 bail. 
CAROLYN KUSKY 
