<P>
WHO REALLY PAYS INSURANCE CLAIMS? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In reading the article regarding the lawsuit filed by Linda Hodges against 
Curtis Cooper, his mother, Crystal Cooper, and their landlady, Olga Kaczmar, in 
connection with the death of Sara Nan Hodges, I was appalled at Hodges' 
statement: "I wouldn't ever take a cent from Olga personally. 
</P>
<P>
