<HEADLINE>
<P>
WARRANT OUT FOR EX-SANTA ANA LAWYER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN FRANCISCO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An arrest warrant has been issued for a former Santa Ana lawyer suspected of 
jumping bail while awaiting trial on charges of masterminding a cocaine ring 
linked to drug lords in Colombia. 
</P>
<P>
Josue T. Prada, 40, scheduled to go on trial May 22 in federal court, failed to 
report to authorities as required under the terms of his bail, U.S. Atty. 
William McGivern said Wednesday. The Drug Enforcement Agency said it was 
considering Prada a fugitive. 
</P>
<P>
Prada, who was born in Bogota, Colombia, but now lives in San Jose, is accused 
of being the kingpin in California for a drug ring that allegedly imported up 
to 2,000 pounds of cocaine, worth as much as $16 million, every year. 
</P>
