<TEXT>
<P>
Magnus Andersson scored six points as world champion Sweden defeated the United 
States 25-20 today in the opening match of the Japan Cup team handball 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Sweden led 15-8 in the first half, but the United States rallied in the second 
half with 12 points to Sweden's 10. Matt Ryan scored four points for the United 
States. 
</P>
<P>
In the women's competition, South Korea trounced Japan 30-19. 
</P>
<P>
Sweden, the United States and Japan are competing in the men's round-robin 
competition and Japan, South Korea and France are participating in the women's 
competition. 
